                  <div id="innerbodycontent" class="row nolayout"><div class="offset1 span10">
            <div id="sm-cog-elements" class="noprint"></div>
            <div class="allset-page-heading"><h1>Reference:Short-term Spoken Chinese: Threshold Vol. 2 (汉语口语入门篇下)</h1></div>
            <!-- subtitle -->
            <div id="contentSub" ><span class="mw-redirectedfrom">(Redirected from <a href="https://resources.allsetlearning.com/gramwiki/?title=Short-term_Spoken_Chinese:_Threshold_Vol._2_(%E6%B1%89%E8%AF%AD%E5%8F%A3%E8%AF%AD%E5%85%A5%E9%97%A8%E7%AF%87%E4%B8%8B)&amp;redirect=no" class="mw-redirect" title="Short-term Spoken Chinese: Threshold Vol. 2 (汉语口语入门篇下)">Short-term Spoken Chinese: Threshold Vol. 2 (汉语口语入门篇下)</a>)</span></div>
            <!-- /subtitle -->
                        <div id="mw-content-text" lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr"><div class="mw-parser-output"><p><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/7561913656/ref%3das_li_ss_tl?ie=UTF8&amp;tag=allset-20&amp;linkCode=as2&amp;camp=217145&amp;creative=399369&amp;creativeASIN=7561913656"><img class="alignright" src="https&#58;//images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/I/51nFO9pR1rL._SL500_AA300_.jpg" /></a>
</p><p><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/7561913656/ref%3das_li_ss_tl?ie=UTF8&amp;tag=allset-20&amp;linkCode=as2&amp;camp=217145&amp;creative=399369&amp;creativeASIN=7561913656">Short-term Spoken Chinese: Threshold Vol. 2 (汉语口语入门篇下) </a> by Ma Jianfei
</p>
<blockquote><p>Short-term Spoken Chinese is the set of textbook for short-term intensive training programs for foreigners. It includes 5 levels of study. The Threshold volumes are for the beginners which include basic words and sentence patterns for communication in daily life.</p></blockquote>
<p><br />
</p>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Grammar_Points_by_Chapter">Grammar Points by Chapter</span></h2>
<ol><li>Lesson Sixteen
<ul><li>动作的进行 The progressive aspect of an action</li>
<li>有的...,有的... The construction "有的...有的..."</li>
<li>用"一边...一边..." The construction "一边...一边..."</li></ul></li>
<li>Lesson Seventeen
<ul><li>动态助词"了" Aspect particle "了"</li>
<li>"...了...就..."格式 The construction "...了...就..."</li></ul></li>
<li>Lesson Eighteen
<ul><li>语气助词"了" Modal particle "了"</li>
<li>"要...了"格式 The construction "要...了"</li>
<li>能愿动词(2) Modal Verbs(2)</li></ul></li>
<li>Lesson Nineteen
<ul><li>程度补语 Complement of degree</li>
<li>能愿动词(3) Modal Verbs (3)</li></ul></li>
<li>Lesson Twenty
<ul><li>时量补语 The time-measure complement</li>
<li>副词"就"与"才" The adverbs "就" and "才"</li>
<li>虽然...但是... The construction "虽然...但是..."</li></ul></li>
<li>Lesson Twenty One
<ul><li>动态助词"过" The aspect particle "过"</li>
<li>"是...的" The construction "是...的"</li>
<li>动量补语 The action-measure complement</li></ul></li>
<li>Lesson Twenty Two
<ul><li>动作的特续 The continuous aspect of an action</li>
<li>结构助词"地" The structural particle "地"</li>
<li>形容词重叠 Reduplication of adjectives</li></ul></li>
<li>Lesson Twenty Three
<ul><li>结果补语 The resultant complement</li>
<li>"到"做结果补语 "到" used as a resultant complement</li>
<li>"住"作结果补语 "住" used as a resultant complement</li>
<li>"一...就..." The construction "一...就..."</li></ul></li>
<li>Lesson Twenty Four
<ul><li>趋向补语 The directional complement</li>
<li>"要是...,就" The construction "要是...,就..."</li>
<li>兼语句 Pivotal Sentence</li></ul></li>
<li>Lesson Twenty Five
<ul><li>可能补语 The potential complement</li>
<li>"了(liăo)" 作可能补语 The potential complement "了"</li>
<li>"怎么(能)...呢" The construction "怎么(能)...呢"</li></ul></li>
<li>Lesson Twenty Six
<ul><li>用"比"表示比较 "比" used to express comparison</li>
<li>数量补语 The complements of quantity</li>
<li>"跟...一样" 表示比较 "跟...一样" used to express comparison</li>
<li>用"有"或"没有"表示比较 "有" or "没有" used to express comparison</li></ul></li>
<li>Lesson Twenty Seven
<ul><li>"把" 字句 (1) "把" sentences (1)</li>
<li>"不是...吗?" The construction "不是...吗?"</li></ul></li>
<li>Lesson Twenty Eight
<ul><li>"把" 字句(2) "把" sentences (2)</li></ul></li>
<li>Lesson Twenty Nine
<ul><li>"被"字句 "被" sentences</li>
<li>连...也(都)...  The construction "连...也(都)..."</li>
<li>Lesson Thirty</li>
<li>意义上的被动句 Notional passive sentences</li></ul></li></ol>
